                            <comment id="13180035" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 5 Jan 2012 00:29:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s the patch for book.xml, anyone can review both the content and my english?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13180059" author="stack" created="Thu, 5 Jan 2012 01:04:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Say what a &apos;a single access priority.&apos; is or, up front say what the three levels are (seems like they are in-memory, single-access and multiple-access).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;...and look for the average key size....&quot;: IIRC, the meta data on an hfile has average key size in it (We are calculating it for key and value at least &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/xref/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/io/hfile/HFile.html#362&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hbase.apache.org/xref/org/apache/hadoop/hbase/io/hfile/HFile.html#362&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards &apos;...generate more garbage to pick up by the JVM.&apos;  you could tell people to look in logs since cache prints out hit rate every minute or so&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Otherwise, doc is excellent.  Fix above on commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13180090" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 5 Jan 2012 01:35:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks Stack for the review I improved a few things.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
